        "fragmentId": "19"
      }
    },
    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "id": "1",
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "text": "We revel in and perpetrate the spiritual destruction of others, just as we try to protect those we love. We may strive to be soldiers rather than killers, but this duality to our nature should be recognized.",
              "kind": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "2",
          "user": "symbols bot",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "kind": "reference",
              "reference": {
                "kind": "document",
                "documentId": "symbol.killer"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.the_captain",
        "fragmentId": "20"
      }
    },
    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "id": "1",
          "user": "symbols bot",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "kind": "reference",
              "reference": {
                "kind": "document",
                "documentId": "symbol.blood"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.the_captain",
        "fragmentId": "22"
      }
    },
    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "id": "1",
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "text": "Many give the easy answer of pacifism or neutrality in conflict, or a particular set of principles that can absolve you of it. These answers are denied by the captain.",
              "kind": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.the_captain",
        "fragmentId": "25"
      }
    },
    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "id": "1",
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In a massacre the winning side is not decent, and standing with the losers is fatal."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.the_captain",
        "fragmentId": "26"
      }
    },
    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "id": "1",
          "user": "symbols bot",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "kind": "reference",
              "reference": {
                "kind": "document",
                "documentId": "symbol.woman"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "2",
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The 'woman' in Cohen's symbology may be a literal woman, but may also be any social order that will have you."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.the_captain",
        "fragmentId": "27"
      }
    },
    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "id": "1",
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "tokens": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Places the soldier as a veteran of the Vietnam War."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.the_captain",
        "fragmentId": "30"
      }
    },
